title: Base Map Services in The National Map
name: base-map-services-in-the-national-map
notes: U.S. Geological Survey, Department of the Interior - Base Map Services in The National Map for the National Geospatial Program.  This harvest source serves as the repository for base map services used in The National Map.  Base map services include:  USGS Hydro-NHD, USGS Imagery Only, USGS Imagery Topo, USGS Shaded Relief Only, and USGS Topo.

http://www.usgs.gov/
The USGS is a federal science agency that provides impartial information on the health of our ecosystems and environment, the natural hazards that threaten us, the natural resources we rely on, the impacts of climate and land-use change, and the core science systems that help us provide timely, relevant, and useable information.
